<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: the 4 lvl rule</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Nesif">Nesif</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:34 a.m. 29/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: the 4 lvl rule<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1966" TARGET=_self>Re: the 4 lvl rule</A> (Malark)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>The whole thing is ridiculous. The reeaalll problem is from whiners who just can't accept getting whacked by someone they don't stand a chance against.

<P>A) Free-For All inspires grouping for very obvious reasons.
<BR>B) A 50th lvl char Stomping on newbies is the same as a red dragon moving into the area and Stomping newbies.
<BR>C) Area's with strong guild alliances will notice a sharp difference (Decrease primarily) in the number of PKing regardless of level.
<BR>D) I'd love for a 50th lvl character to come stomping around. Watching an organized army bashing themselves against a God like character would be incredible to see, if nothing else. I'd spend a life or two on it. Of course, since this can never happen, and only a lvl 46+ character can fight of the menace of an invading 50 lvl char...grrrrr
<P>You freakin whiners make me sick, that there should even be a level rule instititued. If you don't want to get whacked DON'T PLAY ON A PVP SERVER PLEASE. THERE IS ONLY ONE AND A LOT OF PPL DON'T WANT IT SCREWED UP MORE THAN IT ALREADY IS! Shew.
<P>Unfortuantely, they won't remove the lvl 4 rule from Rallos, but I think they should remove it for other races, so the 4 lvl rule only applies to players in the same race. Anything else is stupid and for whiners to cry about.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><EM><A HREF="http://www.moonbase.com/doug/" TARGET=_top>My Everquest Adventures</A></EM></P>
